## 2. Onboarding Flows

### 2.1 Customer Onboarding: Inline Profile Completion Modal
To reduce friction and minimize user drop-offs, the customer onboarding flow will utilize an **inline profile completion modal** directly on the OTP verification screen instead of redirecting the user to a dedicated page.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start: /auth/login] --> B[Enter 10-digit Mobile]
    B --> C[Hit /send-otp]
    C --> D[Redirect to /auth/verify]
    D --> E[Enter 6-digit OTP & verify]
    E --> F{New Customer?}
    F -- Yes --> G[Trigger Inline Profile Modal]
    G --> H[Enter Name]
    H --> I[Submit to verify-otp with Name]
    I --> J[Save Token & Redirect to /]
    F -- No --> K[Save Token & Redirect to Dashboard / Home]
```

1.  User enters mobile and OTP.
2.  If the backend `/verify-otp` response indicates a new customer (`{ newCustomer: true }`):
    *   The OTP entry boxes fade out, and a modal slides in on the same screen: *"Welcome to Sahayog Sarthi! Please tell us your name to complete your profile."*
    *   The user types their name and clicks "Complete Profile".
    *   The frontend sends the registration call `POST /api/v1/auth/verify-otp` containing `{ mobile, otp, name }` to create the Mongoose document.
3.  Upon success, the token is saved, and the user is redirected to the homepage `/`.

### 2.2 Worker Onboarding (`/auth/register-worker`)
A clean multi-step onboarding wizard to guide sarthis during registration:

*   **Step 1: Account Details:** Full name, 10-digit mobile number, service category dropdown (Electrician, Plumber, etc.), and experience (in years).
*   **Step 2: Pricing & Geolocation (Optional):**
    *   Hourly rate (in ₹).
    *   **Optional GPS Capture:** The app requests browser geolocation permissions. 
        *   *If allowed:* Coordinates are auto-populated.
        *   *If blocked/declined:* The coordinates are set to a default fallback coordinate (e.g. center of Lucknow `[80.9462, 26.8467]`) and the onboarding flow proceeds without errors.
*   **Step 3: KYC Document Upload:**
    *   Drag-and-drop file uploader (supports PDF, JPG, and PNG up to 5MB, up to 3 files).
*   **Submission:** Hits `/api/v1/auth/register/worker` and uploads the details. Once completed, redirects to `/workers/dashboard`.

